mdElement.text: Model for the domain of relevance to TAP metadata. This includes concept of importance for service specification in Registry, for database metadata in the TAP_SCHEMA and for VOTable-s returning the result of a query. In orange elements from the TAP 0.31 metadata though they have been changed (see attached notes). In purple new elements. In white new elements proposed by Francois Ochsenbein. In grey GROUP and PARAM elements form VOTable. In light yellow is represented the concept of QueryResult that will have some place in the
Added isDefault: if true, this schem's name is not required in queries.
Added viewSQL: the SQL query used to create the view.

Added all attributes from length onwards. Length is used for VARCHAR. Rank gives the order of a column in the table and order in "select *" result. canBeNull is important for knowing when to query with "IS NULL" etc.
If PrimaryKey is accepted the reference to "otherTable" must be removed.

The result of a query will be represented in a VOTable. Conceptually it still has "ADQL" columns, but the Columns in a query result may not require all the metadata that are required of columns in table metadata.
